41.16:
You will winnow them and the wind will blow them away;
the wind will scatter them.
You will rejoice in the Lord;
you will boast in the Holy One of Israel.

41.17:
The oppressed and the poor look for water, but there is none;
their tongues are parched from thirst.
I, the Lord, will respond to their prayers;
I, the God of Israel, will not abandon them.

41.29:
Look, all of them are nothing,
their accomplishments are nonexistent;
their metal images lack any real substance.

42.3:
A crushed reed he will not break,
a dim wick he will not extinguish;
he will faithfully make just decrees.

42.4:
He will not grow dim or be crushed
before establishing justice on the earth;
the coastlands will wait in anticipation for his decrees.”

42.14:
“I have been inactive for a long time;
